2013-01-18 Version 0.2.1

	* JSON as default POST value
	* uses a full-featured config file to push to API
	* still using user/password for authentication
	* handles msgpack also
	* persists according to user choice, or in case of failure
	* configurable several retries in case of failure
	* persist-only and realtime modes available
	* time_cap, time after which the aggregated data is always sent
	* uses gzip compression upon disk storage
	* only supports one type of input data for now, does not fork
